title: Quality Assurance Architect (Networking)
description: We are looking for a Quality Assurance Architect with in-depth knowledge of Python and strong understanding of networking technologies to join PLVision. Our ideal candidate should have profound experience working with enterprise-level software and performing advanced testing, both functional and non-functional.,As a Quality Assurance Architect, you will join our Architecture Office and play a crucial role in ensuring the quality of the innovative products we build for our customers, who value PLVision‚Äôs unique expertise in end-to-end networking software development. We offer numerous opportunities for professional growth in the company with in-demand and future-proof specialization in computer networking.,Client profile,A world‚Äôs leading US-based networking equipment, networking software and switching ASIC (chip) vendor. Their networking products enable turnkey solutions for datacenter, ISP/telcom and enterprise clients.,About PLVision,We are a software product development company specializing in computer networking and embedded systems. PLVision has offices in Krakow, Poland, and in Ukraine: Lviv, Odesa, Kyiv, and Kharkiv (currently relocated). Founded in 2007, the company helps networking industry leaders and ambitious startups in the U.S., Israel, and the EU countries to launch innovative products.,Vacancy responsibilities:,‚Ä¢ Design and implement test automation frameworks for networking products, including switches, routers, smart NICs, and DPUs,‚Ä¢ Develop and execute test plans for networking products to ensure they meet quality standards, including functional and non-functional requirements,‚Ä¢ Collaborate with development teams to ensure that test automation is integrated into the development process and that issues are detected and addressed on time,‚Ä¢ Stay up-to-date with industry trends and best practices for test automation and quality assurance in the networking industry,‚Ä¢ Lead and mentor other members of the Quality Assurance and testing teams,‚Ä¢ Active involvement in open-source communities related to networking products,‚Ä¢  Knowledge of market trends in the networking industry and ability to align test automation strategies with customer product needs,Vacancy requirements:,‚Ä¢ 8+ years of experience in Software Testing and Quality Assurance with a focus on test automation and scripting,‚Ä¢ Proficiency in Python programming language and experience with other scripting languages,‚Ä¢ Test automation frameworks and scripting languages such as pytest, Robot Framework and unittest,‚Ä¢ Experience of working in the networking industry, specifically with switches, routers, smart NICs and DPUs,‚Ä¢ Experience with open-source networking operating systems and software, such as SONiC, DENT, Linux, Open vSwitch and DPDK,‚Ä¢ In-depth knowledge of networking technologies, protocols and architectures, including L2/L3 switching, routing, load balancing and security,‚Ä¢ Strong understanding of networking protocols, including TCP/IP, BGP, OSPF, VLANs and VXLAN,‚Ä¢ Strong understanding of the configuration and operation of switches, routers, smart NICs and DPUs,‚Ä¢ Knowledge of software-defined networking (SDN) concepts and architectures such as OpenFlow and OVSDB,‚Ä¢ Knowledge of network testing and monitoring tools such as Spirent, Ixia,‚Ä¢ Knowledge of network emulation and simulation tools such as GNS3 and NS-3,‚Ä¢ Experience with network testing tools such as Wireshark, tcpdump, ping, etc.,‚Ä¢ Experience with network automation and programmability using such tools as Ansible and REST APIs,‚Ä¢ Knowledge of virtualization and containerization tools such as VirtualBox, Docker and Kubernetes,‚Ä¢ Good understanding of CI/CD processes,‚Ä¢ Strong analytical and problem-solving skills,‚Ä¢ Excellent communication and collaboration skills with the ability to work effectively in a team

Outreach customers complete many calls with their prospects on our voice platform on a daily basis. The Voice Services team is hiring software engineers to increase the momentum in this space. If you have experience in building high availability voice communication systems with open source real-time communication software and commercial communications platform APIs, we‚Äôd love to talk to you about this opportunity. Real-time system development is a little different from other web development. The features we build are inherently heavy on state, complex in workflow, and include extensive third-party integrations. You‚Äôll have to be creative, build on top of a lot of existing technology, and stay focused on Outreach‚Äôs core value proposition of revenue efficiency. You‚Äôll be building systems to ensure calling is simple, reliable, and crystal clear; so that our customers can reduce the time on clicking around or performing repetitive actions and focus on what matters most - interacting with their prospects.,üîπ Working with commercial CPaaS APIs and open-source real-time communication software to manage calls, messages, and security.,üîπ Finding ways to engineer high availability into a system that has lots of moving parts, not all of which are directly under your control.,üîπ Working with stakeholders to make sure our customers have the tools they need to be successful on our platform.,üîπ Finding quick ways to prototype and test possible solutions to large problems.,üîπ Looking up and down the stack for the best return on investment for any given pain point.,üîπ Working on one of the most visible parts of Outreach‚Äôs product - to both our customers and the rest of our organization.,üîπ 6 + years of experience building back-end services and shipping production quality code in Java, Go or C++, along with strong software engineering skills.,üîπ Proven technical and project leadership skills and able to guide and mentor others.,üîπ Experience with cloud-based service applications and continuous-deployment projects.,üîπ Willing to go above and beyond to help other team members.,üîπ Ability to prioritize details along a path of iterative delivery.,üîπ Ability to quickly ramp up new technologies and start contributing.,üîπ Experience with diagnosing real-time media quality issues (plus).,üîπ Experience with VoIP, specifically using WebRTC and SIP to facilitate real-time communication between users and with phone numbers across the globe (plus).,- Own features end-to-end, from the customer need all the way to the back-end implementation.,- Are highly collaborative and distribute technical leadership throughout the team.,- Do Agile development, with Sprints and regular retrospectives.,- Function in a highly progressive, quick-iteration environment focused on delivering consistent, incremental customer value.,- Have something new to demo every week!,We‚Äôre currently shoring up the core functionalities of our telecom product. In the long term we want to give customers the same edge with calling and messaging that they have with email: the ability to optimize and constantly improve how they interact with customers. We will face new challenges as we continue to scale out to ten times the volume of calling we have today and beyond. These efforts present a diverse gamut of work that will help enhance Outreach‚Äôs competitive edge by making our customers more effectively.

You‚Äôre free to distribute those hours throughout the week in the way that you find the most convenient, within reason.,We want to ensure proper work-life balance and create an environment where you can focus on your code while at work, and on whatever brings you pleasure in your free time.,That is why as one of our benefits we offer the services of a private assistant. Appointments, research, online shopping, and more ‚Äì you choose which tasks to pass on to your assistant.,Do you have at least 5 years of programming experience ‚Äì not necessarily professional ‚Äì including at least a year with Python? If so, you have probably written so much Python code in your life that at times you want to express your thoughts through list comprehensions. Thanks to your extensive experience, you can solve any problem that gets thrown at you, but that is not enough ‚Äì you come up with multiple solutions for every issue, and you always know how to choose the most Pythonic one.,And that is all a good sign ‚Äì a sign that means you‚Äôre exactly the type of person that we‚Äôre looking for! If you‚Äôd like to see what it‚Äôs like to work with Python natives who all bring their long-standing expertise to the table, please get in touch. Spoiler alert: it‚Äôs great.,We have good manners, though, so let us introduce ourselves first. Do you want to find out more about the company? We were hoping you‚Äôd ask.,Reef Technologies is a,. We‚Äôre a small, agile, senior-only team. All of our current members have more than seven years of strong experience, so we don‚Äôt ever have anything urgent to fix. We only deliver stable solutions, as we have developed a system that has delivered more than a hundred challenging projects in the last three years. We‚Äôd like to improve it even further with you on the team.,The demand for our work is extremely high, so we get to pick and choose the projects that we want to take on ‚Äì and the same goes for you. Before you get assigned to a project, you‚Äôll get a personal call from the CEO asking whether you‚Äôre interested in that particular task and if you don‚Äôt like it, we‚Äôll just get something else. That‚Äôs the beauty of having a sales team that greatly outperforms our delivery capacity.,At Reef Technologies, we don‚Äôt have managers. Thanks to the group decision-making framework, Sociocracy 3.0, every member of the team can be sure that their opinion will be valued. (Check it out here, you‚Äôll wonder how you‚Äôd survived in traditional organizations until now!),Our CEO doesn‚Äôt only take care of sales, bureaucracy, and client relationships - he is also a programmer, so all of us really do work together and understand the job at hand.,We mainly accept offers from startups and small-to-medium businesses from the US, the UK, and Canada. Some projects may only last a couple of hours, while others take even a few years for us to complete. There is one thing that you can be sure of, though - that it will always be your personal choice whether to work on a particular project or reject it. What would you have thought about these?,* financial data warehouse which aggregates over 31 000 time series into a few hundred charts for a fintech company from London,* graph data search/visualization system for auditors/investigators from Norway,* super scalable WAF optimized down to extremely low running costs for a client from Chicago, IL,* multisource cloud object synthesizer library for a storage provider from San Mateo, CA,* report generator/inventory tracker for an e-commerce/healthcare company from Canada,* k8s-based revenue optimizer for large private GPU compute clusters in North America,* paper product level tracker for toilet cleaners from Canada,* hydrant certification report generator for Australian plumbers,* multi-tenant hospitality management system for large properties in the US,* large scale information display system for retailers (international),We have already delivered those, but you can be sure we‚Äôve got even more exciting projects coming up in the future.,All that without ever setting foot in an office. We have completed those projects ‚Äì and many more ‚Äì from the comfort of our own homes, from tropical beaches and from our favorite coffee shops. Some of us work early in the morning, others start off late in the night. Each of us is free to choose their own programming environment. We know our engineers are competent enough to organize their work and achieve top productivity in their own way. Do you think you'd enjoy this type of freedom? Become one of us and make the world a better place by delivering more than just lines of code.
